BitStream PRD (Product Requirements Document)
Executive Summary
BitStream is an open-source, all-in-one communication platform combining chat, video conferencing, scheduling, and workspace management. Think Slack + Zoom + Calendly + Discord in one unified experience, with a strong focus on context-aware communication and workflow integration.

Vision & Positioning
"One platform for all professional and personal communication needs"
Target users: Remote teams, freelancers, communities, small businesses, and individuals seeking a privacy-focused, self-hostable communication hub.

Core Feature Set
1. Messaging System

Personal Spaces: 1-on-1 DMs with rich media support (files, images, GIFs, code snippets)
Professional Spaces (Groups): Team channels with threading, mentions, reactions
Smart Inbox: Unified view with priority filtering (AI-powered)
Message Actions: Pin, bookmark, schedule send, remind me, translate
Rich Text Editor: Markdown support, code blocks with syntax highlighting
Search: Full-text search across all conversations with filters

2. Real-Time Communication

Voice Calls: 1-on-1 and group voice channels with noise cancellation
Video Calls: HD video (up to 50 participants), screen sharing, virtual backgrounds
Live Streaming: Broadcast mode for webinars/town halls (100+ viewers)
Voice Rooms: Drop-in audio spaces (Discord-style)
Recording & Transcription: Auto-transcribe meetings with searchable text

3. Smart Scheduling & Calendar

Integrated Calendar: Sync with Google/Outlook calendars
Meeting Scheduler: Share availability links (Calendly-style)
Smart Suggestions: AI recommends optimal meeting times across timezones
Meeting Prep: Auto-generate agendas from chat context
Follow-ups: Post-meeting action items extraction and tracking
Timezone Intelligence: Auto-convert times, show local clocks for participants

4. Workspace Management

Dual-Mode Interface:

Professional Mode: Team workspaces with channels, projects
Personal Mode: Friend groups, family chats, hobby communities


Projects & Boards: Kanban boards integrated with chat (light project management)
Shared Docs: Collaborative notes with real-time editing (Notion-lite)
File Hub: Centralized file storage with version control
Polls & Decisions: Quick voting, decision tracking

5. AI-Powered Features (MVP 2.0)

Smart Summaries: Auto-summarize long threads and missed conversations
Meeting Assistant: Real-time transcription, action item extraction
Context Search: "Find when John mentioned the Q4 budget"
Draft Replies: AI suggests message responses
Sentiment Analysis: Team mood tracking (opt-in)

6. Integration Ecosystem

Webhooks & Bots: Custom bot creation with API
Third-party Integrations:

Productivity: Notion, Trello, Asana, Jira
Dev Tools: GitHub, GitLab, Linear
Storage: Google Drive, Dropbox, OneDrive
Automation: Zapier, Make.com


Embeds: Rich previews for links (YouTube, Twitter, Figma, etc.)

7. Privacy & Security

End-to-End Encryption: For private chats (opt-in)
Self-Hosting: Docker deployment for full data control
Granular Permissions: Role-based access control (RBAC)
Audit Logs: Activity tracking for professional workspaces
Data Export: Full data portability (GDPR compliant)

8. Mobile & Desktop Experience

Cross-Platform: Web, macOS, Windows, Linux, iOS, Android
Offline Mode: Queue messages, sync when online
Push Notifications: Smart notification batching
Widgets: Quick access to active chats, upcoming meetings


Additional Feature Ideas (Differentiation)
Contextual Communication

Thread-to-Meeting: Convert chat threads into instant video calls with context preserved
Meeting Continuity: Return to chat with auto-posted summary and recording link
Topic Threads: Auto-organize conversations by detected topics

Focus & Wellbeing

Do Not Disturb Modes: Schedule focus time, auto-decline meetings
Break Reminders: Pomodoro timer integration
Meeting Fatigue Tracker: Warn when calendar is overbooked

Community Features

Public Spaces: Open communities with invite links
Event Management: Host virtual events with ticketing
Live Q&A: Audience questions during streams
Breakout Rooms: Split video calls into sub-groups

Developer Experience

Code Collaboration: Built-in code review tools, snippet sharing
CI/CD Notifications: Build status, deployment alerts
API Playground: Test webhooks directly in-app

Monetization (For Sustainability)

Free Tier: Unlimited messages, 5GB storage, 40-min video calls
Pro Tier: Extended limits, AI features, advanced integrations ($8/user/month)
Enterprise: SSO, compliance features, dedicated support (custom pricing)


