Tech Stack
Frontend

Web: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
UI Library: shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS
State Management: Zustand + React Query
Real-time: Socket.io client
Mobile: React Native (shared codebase)

Backend

API Server: Node.js + Express (or Fastify)
Real-time: Socket.io + Redis Pub/Sub
Database: PostgreSQL (primary) + Redis (cache/sessions)
File Storage: MinIO (S3-compatible, self-hostable)
Search: ElasticSearch (or MeiliSearch for lighter alternative)

Video/Audio

WebRTC: MediaSoup (SFU) or LiveKit (scalable media server)
TURN/STUN: Coturn (for NAT traversal)
Recording: Jitsi Recording or custom FFmpeg pipelines

AI/ML (Optional Layer)

Transcription: Whisper API (OpenAI) or self-hosted Whisper
Summaries: GPT-4 API or open models (LLaMA, Mistral)
Embeddings: Sentence-BERT for semantic search

Infrastructure

Containerization: Docker + Docker Compose
Orchestration: Kubernetes (for scaling) or Docker Swarm
CI/CD: GitHub Actions
Monitoring: Prometheus + Grafana
Logging: ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana)

Authentication

Auth: NextAuth.js or Supertokens
SSO: SAML 2.0, OAuth 2.0 (Google, GitHub, Microsoft)


Strong Use Cases

Remote Startups: Replace Slack + Zoom + Calendly with one tool
Freelancer Collectives: Manage clients and projects in separate workspaces
Open Source Communities: Self-hosted discussions with video meetups
Educational Groups: Study groups with screen sharing and scheduling
Gaming Clans: Voice rooms + personal chats (Discord alternative)
Healthcare Teams: HIPAA-compliant self-hosted option
Privacy-Conscious Users: End-to-end encrypted, self-hostable alternative


Success Metrics

Engagement: Daily Active Users (DAU), messages sent, calls made
Retention: Week 1, Month 1, Month 3 retention rates
Performance: <200ms message latency, <5s video call setup
Community: GitHub stars, contributor count, Docker pulls


Competitive Advantage

Open Source: Full transparency, community-driven
Self-Hostable: Data sovereignty, no vendor lock-in
All-in-One: Reduce tool sprawl
Context-Aware: AI that understands your workflow
Freemium Done Right: Generous free tier, fair paid features


Resume Highlights
"Built BitStream, an open-source unified communication platform combining real-time messaging, video conferencing, and smart scheduling. Architected scalable WebRTC infrastructure handling 1000+ concurrent users. Implemented AI-powered meeting transcription and contextual search using NLP models. Stack: React, Node.js, PostgreSQL, WebRTC (MediaSoup), Docker."

Next Steps: Start with MVP 1.0, build in public, gather feedback on GitHub, iterate rapidly. Focus on polish and performance over feature bloat.
